<subSubSection id="34F177A62E4FEF51FF54F8A0FE637F6A" lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7C54242D2E4FEF51FF54F8A0FE637F6A" blockId="50.[189,1399,1465,1984]" lastBlockId="51.[242,1399,267,323]" lastPageId="51" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="187A59DC2E4FEF50FE2FF8A0FDC57949" author="Kukuev E. I. &amp; Parin N. V. &amp; Trunov I. A." box="[393,624,1864,1888]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="185 - 199" refId="ref40826" refString="Kukuev E. I., Parin N. V. &amp; Trunov I. A. 2012. Materials for the revision of the Family Caristiidae (Perciformes). 2. Manefishes from the East Atlantic (Redescription of Platyberyx opalescens Zugmayer and description of two new species Platyberyx mauli sp. n. and Caristius andriashevi sp. n.). Journal of Ichthyology 52 (3): 185 - 199. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1134 / S 0032945212010080" type="journal article" year="2012">
Kukuev 
<emphasis id="4E9FF83F2E4FEF50FE40F8A1FDA87949" box="[486,541,1864,1888]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
, reliable catches of 
<taxonomicName id="BBEB5FAE2E4FEF50FCEDF8A1FC697949" authorityName="Zugmayer" authorityYear="1911" box="[843,988,1864,1888]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Caristiidae" genus="Platyberyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opalescens">
<emphasis id="4E9FF83F2E4FEF50FCEDF8A1FC697949" box="[843,988,1864,1888]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">P. opalescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known from 
<collectingCountry id="04FC64BD2E4FEF50FB3AF8A0FB437949" box="[1180,1270,1864,1888]" name="Portugal" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Portugal</collectingCountry>
to northern 
<collectingCountry id="04FC64BD2E4FEF50FF54F880FED279A9" box="[242,359,1896,1920]" name="Mauritania" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Mauritania</collectingCountry>
and suggest that the range of the species includes the near-bottom waters of the continental slope (bathial-pelagic ichthyocene) of the East Atlantic. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="187A59DC2E4FEF50FC12F860FB247989" author="Santos R. S. &amp; Porteiro F. M. &amp; Barreiros J. P." box="[948,1169,1928,1952]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" pagination="1 - 244" refId="ref43831" refString="Santos R. S., Porteiro F. M. &amp; Barreiros J. P. 1997. Marine fishes of the Azores: annotated checklist and bibliography. Arquipelago - Life and Marine Sciences. Suppl. 1: 1 - 244." type="journal article" year="1997">
Santos 
<emphasis id="4E9FF83F2E4FEF50FBA3F861FB8B7989" box="[1029,1086,1928,1952]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">et al.</emphasis>
(1997)
</bibRefCitation>
, the presence of this species off the Azores is based on the identification of a 
<quantity id="BB1389C82E4FEF50FC9BF840FC3279E9" box="[829,903,1960,1984]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="mm" value="63.0">63 mm</quantity>
specimen caught by the R/V “Michael Sars” at 
<geoCoordinate id="19DF42EA2E4EEF51FF54FEE3FEC57F0A" box="[242,368,267,291]" degrees="29.7833" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" precision="5" value="-29.7833">29.7833º W</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="19DF42EA2E4EEF51FEDFFEE3FE457F0A" box="[377,496,267,291]" degrees="36.8833" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" precision="5" value="36.8833">36.8833º N</geoCoordinate>
(St. 56). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="187A59DC2E4EEF51FD47FEE3FC117F0A" author="Eschmeyer W. N." box="[737,932,267,291]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref39931" refString="Eschmeyer W. N. (ed.) 2013. The Catalog of Fishes. California Academy of Sciences, San Francisco, California, U. S. A. Available from: http: // researcharchive. calacademy. org / research / ichthyology / catalog / fishcatmain. asp and http: // collections. calacademy. org / ich /" type="url" year="2013">Eschmeyer (2013)</bibRefCitation>
the range of the species is wider (
<collectingCountry id="04FC64BD2E4EEF51FAA0FEE3FAC27F0A" box="[1286,1399,267,291]" name="Greenland" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Greenland</collectingCountry>
and eastern Atlantic).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
